<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-657-233  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 657 233.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Dec 3 1990 v7 n48 p29(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Feldstar packs more features into data-analysis package. (FeldstarSoftware Inc.'s Analyst One 1.2) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ferranti, Marc.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Feldstar Software Inc introduces Analyst One 1.2, a $199multidimensional data analysis tool.andP;  Analyst One goes beyond thefunctions of normal spreadsheets because it is designed to comparevariables over time using historical data that is stored in arelational data base engine.andP;  Version 1.2 features a newwave-graph function for comparing data from different time periodson the same graph.andP;  Also new to the package is a globalrecalculation feature that will globally modify all data if a dataentry error is discovered.andP;  Analyst One has many of the samefeatures as more expensive programs but requires only 512Kbytes ofmemory and two megabytes of disk space.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Feldstar Software Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Analyst One 1.2 (Data analysis software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionData AnalysisSpreadsheetsSoftware PackagesData Representation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Marc FerrantiandM;A new version of Analyst One, a multidimensional data-analysis tool, had beenattracting a growing number of early users looking for a low-cost,low-overhead program that expands the boundaries of traditional spreadsheets.andM;Analyst One 1.2, released last month, manages to cram features such as newmenus, a wave-graph format and global recalculation capabilities into a $199package that requires only 512K bytes of memory and a couple of megabytes ofdisk space, said John Hoskins, president of developer Feldstar Software Inc.andO;in Dallas.andM;The new recalculation feature makes it easier to globally modify historicaldata when a data-entry error is discovered, he said.andP;  The wave graph allowsusers to view data from different time periods on the same line graph, headded.andM;The tool stores historical data in a relational database engine and letsusers call up and compare any variables they want from the database inrow-and-column format.andM;Beta testers were particularly impressed with the graphing feature becausewhat sets multidimensional analysis apart from the traditionaltwo-dimensional spreadsheets is its ability to compare multiple variablesover time.andM;&quot;We need to be able to look at expenses by region over time,&quot; said DianeAltweis, a cost accountant at ConServCo, a health-care management firm inTampa, Fla.andP;  &quot;The old spreadsheets can't look at these numbersthree-dimensionally.&quot;andM;A number of multidimensional analysis toolsor example, the recently releasedLotus Improv for the NeXT machine and ManageWare Inc.'s Compete forWindowsave expanded the boundaries of the traditional 2- spreadsheet.andP;  Andnewer versions of old standards, such as Lotus 1-2-3 3.1, offer somecapability to examine several variables over time, Altweis said.andP;  &quot;But theyrequire at least a meg of memory, several megs of extended memory and costmore than Analyst One,&quot; she said.andM;In the new version, Feldstar has added several ease-of-use features.andP;  Forexample, Analyst One now guides users through the program by allowing them tohit the F2 key at any point in the program to bring up pick lists andpoint-and-shoot menus.andM;Users also can input eight-character variable names, and network users canreconfigure graphics and printer drivers on the fly.andM;Current users can upgrade for free.andP;  Feldstar can be reached at (214)407-1006.andO;</TEXT></DOC>